North, Southern Sudan Parties Agree on Border Security, African Union Says

-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 
2011-05-31T05:59:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-31/north-southern-sudan-parties-agree-on-border-security-african-union-says.html
Sudan ’s ruling  National Congress
Party  and Southern Sudan’s Sudan People’s Liberation Movement
signed an agreement on border security yesterday, the African
Union said.  The accord establishes a common border zone between
northern and southern Sudan that is to be demilitarized and
jointly monitored and patrolled, the Addis Ababa-based
continental body said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  